1
00:00:03,128 --> 00:00:05,088
[theme song playing]

2
00:01:22,416 --> 00:01:28,338
DOUBT

3
00:01:33,510 --> 00:01:34,553
[tennis ball thwacking]

4
00:01:38,181 --> 00:01:40,684
[Light] I have to admit,
I was surprised, Ryuga.

5
00:01:40,892 --> 00:01:42,341
I never thought
you'd ask me to play tennis

6
00:01:42,416 --> 00:01:43,770
as a way to get to know each other.

7
00:01:44,396 --> 00:01:45,772
Is it a problem for you?

8
00:01:45,856 --> 00:01:46,815
[Light] Not at all.

9
00:01:47,232 --> 00:01:49,359
But when you first invited me to play,

10
00:01:49,484 --> 00:01:50,819
did you know how good I was?

11
00:01:51,361 --> 00:01:53,030
Yes. I'll be fine, though.

12
00:01:53,488 --> 00:01:54,406
It's been a while

13
00:01:54,489 --> 00:01:57,451
but at one time I was actually
the British Junior Champion.

14
00:01:57,951 --> 00:01:59,494
[Light] If I ask him if he's British,

15
00:01:59,578 --> 00:02:01,622
would he think I'm trying
to find out more about him

16
00:02:01,747 --> 00:02:02,914
because I'm Kira?

17
00:02:03,290 --> 00:02:05,083
Well, can't hurt to try.

18
00:02:05,709 --> 00:02:07,711
Ryuga, were you raised in the UK?

19
00:02:07,878 --> 00:02:10,756
I lived in England for about five years
when I was younger.

20
00:02:10,881 --> 00:02:12,049
But save your breath.

21
00:02:13,008 --> 00:02:15,385
Nothing in that story
would reveal L's true identity,

22
00:02:15,469 --> 00:02:16,345
I promise you.

23
00:02:16,928 --> 00:02:18,930
Oh, is that so?

24
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:21,224
[L] Well, since it's our first match,

25
00:02:21,308 --> 00:02:22,851
why don't we just play a single set?

26
00:02:22,976 --> 00:02:25,354
-First one to six?
-[Light] That's fine by me.

27
00:02:31,735 --> 00:02:35,030
This is just a friendly game of tennis.
Nothing more.

28
00:02:35,405 --> 00:02:38,784
In and of itself it won't determine
if Light is Kira.

29
00:02:39,368 --> 00:02:41,536
But I know Kira hates to lose.

30
00:02:43,914 --> 00:02:44,790
[grunts]

31
00:02:45,374 --> 00:02:46,833
[yelps]

32
00:02:49,753 --> 00:02:51,088
[L] Fifteen, love.

33
00:02:52,631 --> 00:02:55,258
Wow, Ryuga. You sure don't mess around.

34
00:02:55,801 --> 00:02:57,511
He who strike first, wins.

35
00:02:58,261 --> 00:03:00,305
[man] What do you mean
you're not at liberty to say?

36
00:03:00,681 --> 00:03:02,265
I'm very sorry, sir.

37
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:05,811
We're under orders from L
not to discuss the case with anyone,

38
00:03:05,894 --> 00:03:06,770
including you.

39
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:10,190
I'm not asking for details here,
just what you're doing and where.

40
00:03:10,649 --> 00:03:12,275
I'm very sorry, sir.

41
00:03:13,235 --> 00:03:14,695
[growls]

42
00:03:16,279 --> 00:03:17,489
[man] You know, Yagami,

43
00:03:17,572 --> 00:03:20,575
it's been more than four months since
this case came to the public's attention

44
00:03:20,659 --> 00:03:21,827
and they want results.

45
00:03:22,536 --> 00:03:24,830
[man] People are saying that the NPA
is incompetent.

46
00:03:24,996 --> 00:03:26,289
That L is incompetent.

47
00:03:26,373 --> 00:03:27,958
With all due respect, sir.

48
00:03:28,291 --> 00:03:31,169
The rest of the department runs away
with their tails between their legs

49
00:03:31,253 --> 00:03:32,379
and we are incompetent?

50
00:03:32,504 --> 00:03:33,672
Do you have any idea

51
00:03:33,755 --> 00:03:36,633
how many people are left
at task force headquarters these days?

52
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:38,719
If you're concerned with public opinion,

53
00:03:38,844 --> 00:03:41,221
then you want to suppress the fact
that most of our detectives

54
00:03:41,388 --> 00:03:44,474
would rather a serial killer roam free
then risk their lives.

55
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:47,519
Please, excuse me.

56
00:03:49,354 --> 00:03:50,439
[man] Yagami.

57
00:03:50,897 --> 00:03:52,691
[man] What about this L character?

58
00:03:53,024 --> 00:03:54,401
Can he be trusted?

59
00:03:56,486 --> 00:03:59,531
[Yagami] In my opinion,
he is a lot more capable than we are.

60
00:03:59,614 --> 00:04:01,700
Right now, even as we speak,

61
00:04:01,783 --> 00:04:03,034
he is risking his life.

62
00:04:04,578 --> 00:04:05,454
[grunts]

63
00:04:06,830 --> 00:04:07,706
[Light grunts]

64
00:04:08,457 --> 00:04:10,125
Are these two really amateurs?

65
00:04:10,292 --> 00:04:11,626
Who are they, anyway?

66
00:04:11,835 --> 00:04:14,421
I think their names are
Light Yagami and Hideki Ryuga.

67
00:04:14,671 --> 00:04:17,424
These are the same two guys
who scored perfect on the exam.

68
00:04:18,592 --> 00:04:19,801
[L] Relax, Light.

69
00:04:19,885 --> 00:04:21,845
While it's true that Kira hates losing,

70
00:04:21,928 --> 00:04:25,348
it's also true that most people would
rather win than lose. It's human nature.

71
00:04:26,391 --> 00:04:29,144
[Light] Is he going to think that I'm Kira
if I go for the win?

72
00:04:29,311 --> 00:04:31,062
I suppose I could just lose on purpose,

73
00:04:31,229 --> 00:04:32,981
but if I do, it could work against me.

74
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:35,192
Since he'd expect Kira to want to win,

75
00:04:35,317 --> 00:04:38,111
he might also expect me to throw the match
to avoid suspicion.

76
00:04:38,945 --> 00:04:42,491
[Light] I don't see any way that he can
profile me based on a tennis match.

77
00:04:42,741 --> 00:04:46,161
So, I have to assume
he has some other goal in mind.

78
00:04:47,245 --> 00:04:48,121
[grunts]

79
00:04:48,455 --> 00:04:49,623
But either way,

80
00:04:49,706 --> 00:04:52,334
I'm not going to let him win!

81
00:04:52,626 --> 00:04:54,044
[Ryuga grunts]

82
00:04:56,505 --> 00:04:59,466
[L] Look at that.
He's going for the win.

83
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,218
That's four games all.

84
00:05:01,384 --> 00:05:03,053
Light Yagami to serve.

85
00:05:03,220 --> 00:05:05,597
[chuckles] And just like that,

86
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,891
we've got an umpire and a line judge.

87
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:10,393
[panting] You won't believe this!

88
00:05:10,519 --> 00:05:12,646
I thought I'd heard the name
Light Yagami somewhere before,

89
00:05:12,729 --> 00:05:13,647
so I checked.

90
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:16,316
He was the '02/'03
Junior High Tennis Champion.

91
00:05:16,441 --> 00:05:18,902
Apparently, during the third year
award ceremony

92
00:05:18,985 --> 00:05:20,779
he announced that he was
hanging up his racket.

93
00:05:20,946 --> 00:05:23,073
And I guess he hasn't
played competitively since.

94
00:05:23,782 --> 00:05:25,700
[female student] Hey, hey!
What about my Ryuga?

95
00:05:25,784 --> 00:05:27,828
Don't tell me you haven't noticed
him holding his own

96
00:05:27,911 --> 00:05:29,996
against this former junior high champ.

97
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:30,956
Hm.

98
00:05:31,832 --> 00:05:34,000
[L] I can see the wheels turning,
Light Yagami.

99
00:05:34,209 --> 00:05:35,627
I'm already in your head.

100
00:05:36,253 --> 00:05:38,839
[Light] There's no way this tennis match
will deepen our friendship.

101
00:05:39,005 --> 00:05:40,131
This is a token gesture.

102
00:05:40,215 --> 00:05:43,677
An elaborate act to go with
so we can say we are closer.

103
00:05:44,302 --> 00:05:46,137
[L] Because I wanted
to play tennis with you,

104
00:05:46,221 --> 00:05:48,306
you'll assume I'm preparing
to take a step closer,

105
00:05:48,473 --> 00:05:50,350
laying the ground work
to get to know you better.

106
00:05:52,185 --> 00:05:53,979
[Light] And then you're going
to try and trap me

107
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:56,898
by getting me to say something
that only Kira would know.

108
00:05:57,065 --> 00:05:58,692
[L] However, I'm sure you will tell me

109
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:00,694
you need to know
if you can trust me first,

110
00:06:00,819 --> 00:06:02,529
and of course,
the only way to win your trust,

111
00:06:02,654 --> 00:06:04,990
will be to share what I know about Kira.

112
00:06:05,365 --> 00:06:07,200
[Light] If you want me
to discuss Kira with you,

113
00:06:07,325 --> 00:06:09,786
it would only make sense
that I want to ask for proof

114
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:12,038
that you are in charge
of the investigation.

115
00:06:12,163 --> 00:06:15,333
And more importantly, that you are
really L, as you've say you are.

116
00:06:15,417 --> 00:06:16,751
[L] So, it goes without saying

117
00:06:16,835 --> 00:06:19,004
that the first thing
you're going to want from me is...

118
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,715
[Light] ...some kind of confirmation

119
00:06:21,965 --> 00:06:24,509
from a third party that you really are L.

120
00:06:24,676 --> 00:06:26,136
[Light] Which means...

121
00:06:26,219 --> 00:06:28,513
[both] We'll have to go
to task force headquarters!

122
00:06:29,180 --> 00:06:32,058
[Light] In all things, one cannot win
with defense alone.

123
00:06:32,475 --> 00:06:34,811
To win, you must attack!

124
00:06:37,105 --> 00:06:38,315
Game and set.

125
00:06:38,523 --> 00:06:40,358
Won by Light Yagami.

126
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:42,110
Six games to four!

127
00:06:42,319 --> 00:06:44,779
[spectators applauding]

128
00:06:46,364 --> 00:06:47,657
[birds chirping]

129
00:06:47,908 --> 00:06:50,285
[L] Just as I expected, you beat me.

130
00:06:50,535 --> 00:06:52,996
[Light] It's been a while
since I had to play that hard.

131
00:06:54,247 --> 00:06:55,498
I'm feeling kind of thirsty.

132
00:06:55,665 --> 00:06:57,834
Plus, there's something
that I wanted to ask you about.

133
00:06:57,959 --> 00:06:59,669
Do you want to go somewhere
for a drink?

134
00:06:59,794 --> 00:07:01,588
You humored me with the tennis match.

135
00:07:01,922 --> 00:07:04,215
The least I can do,
is answer some of your questions.

136
00:07:04,925 --> 00:07:07,010
But before this conversation
goes any further,

137
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:08,511
there's something I must tell you.

138
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:10,305
What's that?

139
00:07:11,139 --> 00:07:14,559
I suspect that you, Light Yagami,
are in fact Kira.

140
00:07:15,060 --> 00:07:17,729
Now, if you still wanna ask me something,
than please, go ahead.

141
00:07:22,692 --> 00:07:24,569
[chuckles] You think I'm Kira?

142
00:07:24,903 --> 00:07:26,571
Well, when I say I suspect you,

143
00:07:26,696 --> 00:07:28,406
it's only a one percent possibility.

144
00:07:28,823 --> 00:07:32,410
That aside, I don't mind telling you
that once I'm sure you aren't Kira

145
00:07:32,494 --> 00:07:34,204
and I can verify
that your deductive skills

146
00:07:34,371 --> 00:07:35,872
are as strong as I think they are,

147
00:07:36,164 --> 00:07:39,292
I'd like nothing more than to have you
work with me on this investigation.

148
00:07:42,921 --> 00:07:44,172
One percent, huh?

149
00:07:44,673 --> 00:07:45,882
That was well worded.

150
00:07:46,257 --> 00:07:48,969
Because no matter how little he says
he suspects me,

151
00:07:49,219 --> 00:07:52,847
it means he has grounds to prevent me
from meeting anyone on the task force.

152
00:07:53,473 --> 00:07:55,684
[Light] It was quite a pre-emptive move
on his part.

153
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:57,519
He got me.

154
00:08:00,772 --> 00:08:03,316
This coffee shop is one of my favorites
in the area.

155
00:08:03,483 --> 00:08:06,611
And if we sit here, there's no chance
of anyone overhearing us.

156
00:08:07,278 --> 00:08:09,990
[L] Thanks for showing me this place.
I can see why you like it.

157
00:08:10,073 --> 00:08:12,117
Not to mention,
we're so out of the way here,

158
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:14,786
no one is gonna give you a hard time
about the way you sit.

159
00:08:14,869 --> 00:08:18,206
I don't sit like this because I want to.
I have to sit like this.

160
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:19,791
You see, if I were to sit normally,

161
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:23,044
my deductive skills would immediately
be reduced by roughly 40 percent.

162
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:26,089
So, what was it you wanted to ask me?

163
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:27,090
[Light] Right.

164
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:28,967
I'm sure that can wait

165
00:08:29,134 --> 00:08:30,719
until you're convinced that I'm not Kira.

166
00:08:30,885 --> 00:08:33,263
So, please, let's talk
about whatever you want to.

167
00:08:34,097 --> 00:08:36,182
You're under no obligation
to do this, but...

168
00:08:36,307 --> 00:08:37,726
would you mind submitting yourself

169
00:08:37,851 --> 00:08:39,561
to a test of your
deductive reasoning skills?

170
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:41,646
Sure, why not.

171
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:43,064
Sounds like fun.

172
00:08:43,565 --> 00:08:44,607
All right then.

173
00:08:44,816 --> 00:08:46,860
We can begin by taking a look at these.

174
00:08:49,237 --> 00:08:52,032
Photographs of three notes
written by prison inmates

175
00:08:52,157 --> 00:08:53,283
while under Kira's control,

176
00:08:53,408 --> 00:08:54,868
just prior to their deaths.

177
00:08:54,993 --> 00:08:57,120
None of this information
has been made public.

178
00:08:57,579 --> 00:08:59,873
You can take as long as you want
to look them over.

179
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:01,541
Please, let me know what you think.

180
00:09:03,668 --> 00:09:04,878
Very interesting.

181
00:09:05,503 --> 00:09:07,380
[Light] Come on, this is child's play.

182
00:09:07,464 --> 00:09:10,216
There's a print number
on the back of each of these photographs.

183
00:09:11,468 --> 00:09:12,844
If I ignore this fact,

184
00:09:12,927 --> 00:09:14,888
and was still able
to come up with the phrase:

185
00:09:14,971 --> 00:09:17,432
"L, do you know, gods of death
love apples",

186
00:09:17,682 --> 00:09:18,892
what would that mean?

187
00:09:19,059 --> 00:09:22,270
Clearly, if I read it the way Kira
intended on my first attempt,

188
00:09:22,479 --> 00:09:23,813
I'd only look more suspicious.

189
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:26,524
But the fact I'm able
to solve this silly code,

190
00:09:26,608 --> 00:09:28,735
isn't enough on its own
to prove that I'm Kira.

191
00:09:30,195 --> 00:09:33,740
It would be quite amazing to learn
that not only could Kira kill others,

192
00:09:33,865 --> 00:09:35,950
but could also control
his victims actions.

193
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:37,577
I think Kira wrote these,

194
00:09:37,702 --> 00:09:39,746
and it seems he's encoded
a message for you as well.

195
00:09:39,829 --> 00:09:41,164
Almost as if he's mocking you.

196
00:09:42,290 --> 00:09:44,000
If you line these notes up
side by side,

197
00:09:44,084 --> 00:09:46,127
and take a look
at the first letter of every line,

198
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:47,504
it reveals a message.

199
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:49,672
Rearranging it like this...

200
00:09:49,881 --> 00:09:50,882
gives you...

201
00:09:51,758 --> 00:09:53,093
"L, do you know

202
00:09:53,426 --> 00:09:55,136
Gods of Death love apples?"

203
00:09:57,055 --> 00:10:00,183
But there're obvious print numbers
on the back of all these photographs.

204
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:02,393
Arrange it in that order, we get:

205
00:10:03,353 --> 00:10:05,021
"L, do you know

206
00:10:05,313 --> 00:10:07,315
Love apples, Gods of Death "

207
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:09,901
[chuckles] That doesn't sound right.

208
00:10:10,068 --> 00:10:11,111
And based on that,

209
00:10:11,194 --> 00:10:14,072
it's hard to believe that Kira
would've wanted you to read it this way.

210
00:10:14,197 --> 00:10:15,448
[L] That's incorrect.

211
00:10:15,698 --> 00:10:16,574
Huh?

212
00:10:17,117 --> 00:10:19,410
The thing is
there were actually four photographs.

213
00:10:20,245 --> 00:10:22,288
When we add this one, it reads...

214
00:10:23,331 --> 00:10:24,958
"L, do you know?

215
00:10:25,208 --> 00:10:28,169
Gods of Death
who love apples have red hands."

216
00:10:28,878 --> 00:10:29,921
[Light] It's a fake.

217
00:10:30,213 --> 00:10:33,216
I never made any criminal
write the letter in this fourth picture.

218
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:34,843
Is he stupid?

219
00:10:35,635 --> 00:10:37,929
But seeing as I only had
three photographs to work with,

220
00:10:38,054 --> 00:10:39,305
my deduction was perfect.

221
00:10:39,430 --> 00:10:40,723
[L] No, it wasn't.

222
00:10:40,849 --> 00:10:43,059
The truth is, there were four of them.

223
00:10:43,143 --> 00:10:45,687
If you'd figured that out,
it would have been perfect.

224
00:10:46,521 --> 00:10:48,898
Even though you knew
the message was incomplete,

225
00:10:49,023 --> 00:10:51,401
you decided that
there were only three notes.

226
00:10:51,818 --> 00:10:54,195
You never even considered
that there might be a fourth.

227
00:10:54,404 --> 00:10:55,613
What to make of that?

228
00:10:56,030 --> 00:10:56,948
Damn him.

229
00:10:57,073 --> 00:10:59,993
This wasn't just about gauging
my deductive reasoning skills.

230
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:02,203
He wanted to see
what my reaction would be.

231
00:11:02,453 --> 00:11:05,790
If I keep falling for his tricks,
I'll be playing right into his hands.

232
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:07,876
Hmm.

233
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:10,044
Well, you got me there.
I didn't think of that.

234
00:11:10,295 --> 00:11:11,212
In any case,

235
00:11:11,296 --> 00:11:14,465
the likelihood this message
will lead you to Kira is not very great.

236
00:11:14,549 --> 00:11:16,509
Besides, we all know
Gods of Death don't exist.

237
00:11:16,634 --> 00:11:19,846
If you were me,
faced with someone who might be Kira,

238
00:11:19,971 --> 00:11:23,183
how would you go about establishing
this person's innocence or guilt?

239
00:11:23,266 --> 00:11:25,018
You need to be absolutely sure.

240
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:27,353
I would probably try
to get him to say something

241
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:29,230
that was never made public in any way

242
00:11:29,355 --> 00:11:31,191
Something that only Kira could know.

243
00:11:31,733 --> 00:11:33,818
Kinda like what you were doing just now.

244
00:11:34,235 --> 00:11:35,737
[L] Truly amazing.

245
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:37,197
What's incredible

246
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:40,116
is that I've asked countless detectives
that same question

247
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:42,952
and it took most of them minutes
to even come up with an answer.

248
00:11:43,119 --> 00:11:44,245
But you...

249
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:47,165
you immediately thought of a scenario

250
00:11:47,373 --> 00:11:50,043
in which Kira is speaking
directly to the investigator.

251
00:11:50,501 --> 00:11:51,628
I'm impressed.

252
00:11:51,836 --> 00:11:53,838
You'll make a fine detective, Light.

253
00:11:54,339 --> 00:11:55,423
[chuckles]

254
00:11:55,506 --> 00:11:57,508
But it's a bit of double-edged sword.

255
00:11:57,634 --> 00:12:00,637
The more impressive my answers,
the more of a suspect I become.

256
00:12:00,845 --> 00:12:02,972
[L] Yes, it's about three percent now.

257
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:06,434
However, it's made me
that much more determined

258
00:12:06,559 --> 00:12:08,770
to work with you on this investigation.

259
00:12:09,604 --> 00:12:12,774
You see, I'm in a position
where even if you are Kira,

260
00:12:12,941 --> 00:12:16,194
it would still be to my benefit
to have you working alongside us.

261
00:12:16,694 --> 00:12:18,071
Do you know why I'd say that?

262
00:12:19,489 --> 00:12:20,782
If I cooperate with you,

263
00:12:20,907 --> 00:12:23,534
there's a chance I can
help the investigation to move forward.

264
00:12:23,993 --> 00:12:26,287
And if I'm Kira, I might reveal myself.

265
00:12:26,871 --> 00:12:28,748
In other words, whether I am Kira or not,

266
00:12:28,873 --> 00:12:30,166
you stand to gain either way.

267
00:12:31,042 --> 00:12:32,669
It’s a very smart move on your part.

268
00:12:33,378 --> 00:12:35,463
But I think you might be
getting the wrong idea.

269
00:12:35,630 --> 00:12:37,840
It's true that I do have
an interest in the Kira case,

270
00:12:37,966 --> 00:12:40,093
and yes, detective work
is a hobby of mine.

271
00:12:40,885 --> 00:12:42,387
But I know that I'm not Kira,

272
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:44,430
and I certainly
don't want to be killed by him.

273
00:12:44,973 --> 00:12:46,933
Besides, what proof
have you been able to give me

274
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:48,726
that you yourself aren't Kira?

275
00:12:49,102 --> 00:12:50,603
I mean, it hardly seems fair

276
00:12:50,687 --> 00:12:52,939
for just one of to be investigated,
wouldn't you say?

277
00:12:53,106 --> 00:12:55,900
At this point, neither of us
can prove that we're not Kira.

278
00:12:56,567 --> 00:12:58,278
However, if you are in fact L,

279
00:12:58,361 --> 00:13:00,780
I don't imagine it would be that hard
for you to prove it to me.

280
00:13:01,114 --> 00:13:02,198
I think I'd be convinced

281
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:05,618
if, say, my father or someone else
from the task force headquarters

282
00:13:05,743 --> 00:13:07,495
was able to confirm your identity.

283
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:11,249
If you can't do that, then I'm afraid
I just won't be able to help you.

284
00:13:12,709 --> 00:13:15,044
You sure talk a lot, don't you, Light?

285
00:13:15,295 --> 00:13:17,422
Typical for someone who hates losing.

286
00:13:17,839 --> 00:13:19,549
I think that's seven percent...

287
00:13:19,882 --> 00:13:21,175
Could it really be him?

288
00:13:22,635 --> 00:13:25,847
I don't remember saying you couldn't meet
anyone from task force headquarters.

289
00:13:25,972 --> 00:13:27,181
to verify my identity.

290
00:13:27,473 --> 00:13:28,433
Huh?

291
00:13:28,558 --> 00:13:30,810
I'm currently working
alongside your father,

292
00:13:30,935 --> 00:13:33,646
as well as several other
senior detectives from the NPA.

293
00:13:34,564 --> 00:13:36,232
Now, if I understand you correctly

294
00:13:36,357 --> 00:13:38,276
and I take you
to task force headquarters,

295
00:13:38,359 --> 00:13:40,278
you'll help us with the investigation.

296
00:13:40,486 --> 00:13:42,447
Am I safe in making this assumption?

297
00:13:43,531 --> 00:13:45,158
[Light] Does this guy have a death wish?

298
00:13:45,533 --> 00:13:47,285
I don't understand. What's he thinking?

299
00:13:47,410 --> 00:13:48,786
[phone ringing]

300
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:50,079
Excuse me.

301
00:13:50,246 --> 00:13:52,040
-[phone buzzing]
-Oh, there goes mine.

302
00:13:53,291 --> 00:13:54,334
Yes?

303
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:56,836
[man] Ryuzaki, I have some bad news.

304
00:13:57,378 --> 00:13:59,005
[Sachiko] Light, your father has--

305
00:13:59,255 --> 00:14:00,131
Light, it's your--

306
00:14:01,341 --> 00:14:02,633
My father...

307
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:04,302
He had a heart attack!

308
00:14:22,695 --> 00:14:24,697
[ambulance siren wailing]

309
00:14:25,448 --> 00:14:26,824
[Sachiko] Okay, see you tomorrow.

310
00:14:26,991 --> 00:14:29,202
Have them call home
if you need me to bring anything.

311
00:14:29,410 --> 00:14:31,871
-Light, you take care of him, okay?
-[Light] Sure.

312
00:14:37,627 --> 00:14:40,213
So, the doctors think
stress was the only cause?

313
00:14:40,421 --> 00:14:41,422
Yeah.

314
00:14:41,547 --> 00:14:43,883
To be honest, I thought it was Kira,
when I first collapsed,

315
00:14:43,966 --> 00:14:45,051
but I'll be all right.

316
00:14:45,218 --> 00:14:48,388
It seems I've been pushing myself
a bit too hard lately.

317
00:14:48,471 --> 00:14:49,347
Indeed.

318
00:14:49,472 --> 00:14:50,973
It must have added to your stress

319
00:14:51,099 --> 00:14:53,184
knowing that Light
is a suspect in this investigation.

320
00:14:53,267 --> 00:14:55,019
You actually told my father that?

321
00:14:55,144 --> 00:14:57,939
Yes, in fact, I've told him everything.

322
00:14:58,314 --> 00:15:00,608
It's true he even knows that I'm L.

323
00:15:02,819 --> 00:15:04,028
That's correct.

324
00:15:04,195 --> 00:15:05,571
This man is L.

325
00:15:05,696 --> 00:15:07,115
To protect his identity,

326
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:09,909
we on the task force
refer to him as Ryuzaki.

327
00:15:10,076 --> 00:15:11,953
But make no mistake, it's him.

328
00:15:12,829 --> 00:15:14,455
This guy is the real L.

329
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:15,832
My father wouldn't lie.

330
00:15:15,998 --> 00:15:19,252
The very same man who has been
controlling the police up to this point.

331
00:15:19,502 --> 00:15:22,380
If I get rid of him
and the rest of the investigative team...

332
00:15:22,630 --> 00:15:23,631
No...

333
00:15:23,881 --> 00:15:26,300
No, let's face it.
It wouldn't be that simple.

334
00:15:27,218 --> 00:15:28,553
There's no need to rush.

335
00:15:28,803 --> 00:15:30,596
I have time to sit back and watch.

336
00:15:31,139 --> 00:15:32,223
But for now,

337
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:34,892
I'm the Light Yagami
who's worried for his father.

338
00:15:35,643 --> 00:15:37,478
So, Ryuzaki,

339
00:15:37,728 --> 00:15:39,897
now that you've had the chance
to talk to my son,

340
00:15:39,981 --> 00:15:41,232
is he cleared as a suspect?

341
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:43,276
When I say I suspect him,

342
00:15:43,443 --> 00:15:44,944
you should know it's very minor.

343
00:15:45,278 --> 00:15:47,321
We’ve gone over this
but I'll explain it again.

344
00:15:47,572 --> 00:15:50,366
Not long ago, Kira killed 12 FBI agents

345
00:15:50,491 --> 00:15:51,951
who'd come to Japan to assist us.

346
00:15:52,952 --> 00:15:56,747
They were instructed to follow people
connected to the Japanese police.

347
00:15:57,290 --> 00:15:59,625
One of these agents, Raye Penber,

348
00:15:59,876 --> 00:16:02,420
exhibited unusual behavior
before he died.

349
00:16:03,504 --> 00:16:04,547
I understand.

350
00:16:04,630 --> 00:16:05,965
And I was one of the people

351
00:16:06,090 --> 00:16:08,259
Raye Penber was investigating
before he died.

352
00:16:08,718 --> 00:16:10,636
It only make sense I'd be a suspect.

353
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:12,388
No, to be more precise,

354
00:16:12,555 --> 00:16:14,474
there's no one else you could suspect.

355
00:16:15,725 --> 00:16:18,311
I find Light's deductive powers
quite impressive.

356
00:16:18,895 --> 00:16:20,771
He's always quick and to the point.

357
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:23,649
Ryuga, I'd like to help
with the investigation.

358
00:16:23,983 --> 00:16:25,443
My father has erased any doubts

359
00:16:25,610 --> 00:16:27,612
I might have had
regarding your true identity.

360
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:30,615
Also, I'd like nothing more
than to catch Kira

361
00:16:30,740 --> 00:16:33,034
so I can prove once and for all
that I'm not him.

362
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:34,410
No, Light.

363
00:16:34,869 --> 00:16:37,330
This is a time in your life
when you should be studying

364
00:16:37,497 --> 00:16:38,915
to become a police officer.

365
00:16:39,165 --> 00:16:41,501
It won't be too late to join us
once you're done.

366
00:16:41,792 --> 00:16:43,461
Come on, Dad. What are you talking about?

367
00:16:43,669 --> 00:16:45,546
Who knows how many years that'll take.

368
00:16:46,506 --> 00:16:48,257
Besides, don't you remember my promise?

369
00:16:49,091 --> 00:16:50,927
That if something ever happened to you,

370
00:16:51,969 --> 00:16:54,764
I'd find Kira and make sure
he gets executed.

371
00:16:56,682 --> 00:17:00,228
I refuse to believe that my son
could turn out to be Kira.

372
00:17:00,770 --> 00:17:03,064
[L] This doesn't seem
like an act to me.

373
00:17:03,356 --> 00:17:05,775
Or if it is, it's too cheesy.

374
00:17:06,734 --> 00:17:08,486
[Yagami] Light, listen to me.

375
00:17:09,403 --> 00:17:11,113
Kira is pure evil.

376
00:17:11,405 --> 00:17:13,032
We can all agree on that.

377
00:17:13,241 --> 00:17:14,408
But recently,

378
00:17:14,492 --> 00:17:17,328
I've been thinking of this whole situation
in a different way.

379
00:17:18,246 --> 00:17:19,622
What is truly evil

380
00:17:19,747 --> 00:17:21,207
is the power to kill people.

381
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:24,752
And any person who has come
to possess this kind of power,

382
00:17:24,877 --> 00:17:25,753
is cursed.

383
00:17:26,295 --> 00:17:27,838
No matter how you use it,

384
00:17:27,964 --> 00:17:31,175
no true happiness
can be obtained like that.

385
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:33,261
Not by killing other people.

386
00:17:34,679 --> 00:17:36,305
[L] I think you're absolutely right.

387
00:17:37,390 --> 00:17:39,392
If Kira is just a normal person,

388
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:41,644
who somehow obtained this awful power,

389
00:17:42,186 --> 00:17:43,896
I would say that he's cursed.

390
00:17:44,564 --> 00:17:47,024
Ryuzaki, I'm sorry for all this trouble.

391
00:17:47,149 --> 00:17:50,111
But I'll be back at work
as soon as the doctors let me out of here.

392
00:17:50,444 --> 00:17:51,320
[nurse] Excuse me.

393
00:17:51,946 --> 00:17:54,156
Visiting hours were over ten minutes ago.

394
00:18:01,664 --> 00:18:02,665
[Light] Ryuga.

395
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:05,459
What would it take to get you
to believe that I'm not Kira?

396
00:18:05,626 --> 00:18:07,378
Please, isn't there something?

397
00:18:07,962 --> 00:18:09,922
If you aren't Kira, it won't be necessary.

398
00:18:10,006 --> 00:18:12,300
Let things run their course
and the truth will be revealed.

399
00:18:12,508 --> 00:18:13,926
I can't take this anymore!

400
00:18:14,260 --> 00:18:15,595
Put yourself in my position.

401
00:18:15,678 --> 00:18:18,264
How do you think it feels
to be accused of being Kira?

402
00:18:20,641 --> 00:18:22,768
It was one of the worst feelings ever.

403
00:18:23,102 --> 00:18:25,146
What if you were to lock me up for a month

404
00:18:25,229 --> 00:18:28,274
in a place with no TV or any other kind
of access to the outside world

405
00:18:28,357 --> 00:18:30,318
and keep a constant watch over me?

406
00:18:30,985 --> 00:18:33,779
Would any normal person be willing
to go to such extreme measures

407
00:18:33,904 --> 00:18:35,114
to clear their name?

408
00:18:35,323 --> 00:18:36,407
That's no good.

409
00:18:36,490 --> 00:18:39,702
I can't do anything that would
deprive you of basic human rights.

410
00:18:39,869 --> 00:18:40,995
And furthermore,

411
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:42,163
it's a complete nonsense

412
00:18:42,288 --> 00:18:44,957
for the investigator
to take suggestions from his suspect.

413
00:18:45,249 --> 00:18:46,125
I understand.

414
00:18:47,501 --> 00:18:49,128
[L] Don't worry so much.

415
00:18:49,629 --> 00:18:52,590
Be patient. It will become apparent to us
if you're not Kira.

416
00:18:53,174 --> 00:18:55,968
And listening to that conversation
between you and your father,

417
00:18:56,552 --> 00:18:58,804
I was almost convinced
you might not be him.

418
00:18:59,430 --> 00:19:02,224
Light, please,
take good care of Mr. Yagami.

419
00:19:02,391 --> 00:19:03,726
Oh, one more thing.

420
00:19:03,893 --> 00:19:06,020
I know agreed
to help with the investigation,

421
00:19:06,103 --> 00:19:09,398
but I don't think I'll be able to do much
until my father is healthy again.

422
00:19:09,857 --> 00:19:11,067
Yes, of course.

423
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:12,735
Well then...

424
00:19:16,364 --> 00:19:17,698
Hideki Ryuga.

425
00:19:18,741 --> 00:19:20,034
Ryuzaki.

426
00:19:20,493 --> 00:19:22,787
He's the L I've been fighting
this whole time.

427
00:19:24,121 --> 00:19:25,706
[Light] What is his real name?

428
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:28,626
Light Yagami,

429
00:19:29,126 --> 00:19:31,087
are you not Kira?

430
00:19:32,755 --> 00:19:33,756
Ryuk.

431
00:19:33,923 --> 00:19:34,840
Huh?

432
00:19:35,424 --> 00:19:38,344
I never once felt cursed
since I picked up the Death Note.

433
00:19:38,552 --> 00:19:40,805
In fact, the thought
never even crossed my mind.

434
00:19:41,806 --> 00:19:43,516
I'm happier than I've ever been.

435
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:45,393
All thanks to this power.

436
00:19:46,268 --> 00:19:48,646
[Light] I'm going to create
a perfect world.

437
00:19:49,146 --> 00:19:50,856
[Ryuk] Honestly, I couldn't care less

438
00:19:51,023 --> 00:19:53,567
whether you feel cursed or happy
to have the notebook.

439
00:19:53,984 --> 00:19:56,862
I leave that sentimental crap
to you humans.

440
00:19:57,446 --> 00:19:58,364
But...

441
00:19:58,531 --> 00:20:01,367
normally, humans who come
into contact with the Shinigami

442
00:20:01,534 --> 00:20:03,494
have nothing but misfortune.

443
00:20:07,373 --> 00:20:08,457
[Light] That's interesting.

444
00:20:08,749 --> 00:20:11,544
But I have no intentions
of repeating that pattern.

445
00:20:11,752 --> 00:20:14,588
[Ryuk chuckles] Well, I hope
you're right about that.

446
00:20:16,424 --> 00:20:17,675
[man] What is this crap?

447
00:20:17,967 --> 00:20:20,553
Don't tell me
this is your ideal of a proposal?

448
00:20:20,678 --> 00:20:22,179
Listen, you people must think

449
00:20:22,304 --> 00:20:23,806
that just mentioning Kira's name

450
00:20:23,931 --> 00:20:25,975
is enough to get us
the ratings we need, huh?

451
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:27,101
Well, you're wrong.

452
00:20:27,184 --> 00:20:28,394
Our program gets the ratings

453
00:20:28,477 --> 00:20:31,188
because we cover stories
that the other stations won't touch!

454
00:20:31,272 --> 00:20:32,398
If it bleeds, it leads!

455
00:20:32,732 --> 00:20:33,774
What I need

456
00:20:34,024 --> 00:20:36,861
is a good fricking story.
Not this crap!

457
00:20:37,111 --> 00:20:38,988
Now, get out there and find me a story!

458
00:20:39,321 --> 00:20:41,073
But the police won't talk, sir.

459
00:20:41,282 --> 00:20:43,534
It's been impossible to get details
from them lately.

460
00:20:43,784 --> 00:20:45,828
Idiots! I don't pay you to complain.

461
00:20:45,911 --> 00:20:48,539
And if they won't give you anything,
then get creative!

462
00:20:48,664 --> 00:20:49,665
[knocking on door]

463
00:20:49,832 --> 00:20:50,916
Huh?

464
00:20:51,125 --> 00:20:53,502
Mr. Demegawa, sir, this is for you.

465
00:20:54,503 --> 00:20:55,671
[Demegawa] What is this?

466
00:20:56,922 --> 00:20:58,299
So, who is this from?

467
00:20:58,758 --> 00:20:59,842
Huh?

468
00:21:00,885 --> 00:21:02,928
[laughs]

469
00:21:03,679 --> 00:21:05,806
[Demegawa] Now, this is more like it.

470
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:08,726
This is what I call a story.

471
00:21:08,976 --> 00:21:11,604
It's almost too good to be true.

472
00:21:12,104 --> 00:21:14,315
"A message to the world from Kira.

473
00:21:14,523 --> 00:21:16,484
If you do not broadcast these tapes,

474
00:21:16,609 --> 00:21:20,529
I'll kill your company's
board of directors one by one."

475
00:21:20,696 --> 00:21:22,239
Who wouldn't air these?

476
00:21:22,531 --> 00:21:25,826
If this is for real, our ratings
are gonna go through the roof!

477
00:21:25,951 --> 00:21:26,952
[Demegawa] Holy crap!

478
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:30,247
I'm so excited I feel like
I'm having a heart attack here!

479
00:21:30,372 --> 00:21:36,295
TO BE CONTINUED
